AvActivityHighlight: The covering of new snow is soft.
AvActivityComment: Over a wide area 30 cm of snow, and up to 50 cm in some localities, has fallen above approximately 2000 m. The covering of new snow is soft. Over a wide area new snow is lying on a weakly bonded old snowpack. Towards its base, the snowpack is faceted and weak. Snow profiles and stability tests have confirmed this situation. Avalanches can be released in deeper layers very easily.
Author: Norbert Lanzanasto
